column3: A football player wearing white and cardinal charges down a field with the football.  In the background the crowd is blurred.
A marching band performs at night. Some members are holding saxophones, while one is playing a trombone. The band member in the middle is wearing a kilt.
A marching band in matching red jackets and white hats parades down a street playing brass instruments.
A marching band member is duct-taped to a rotating wheel on a frame being rolled in front of a crowd.

A young woman with sunglasses perched atop a floppy hat, clad in a red blazer and blue tie, plays a saxophone while walking down the street.
Three football players in white and red uniforms charge down a field while spectators watch from the stands behind them.
The Stanford University Marching Band is known for its unique uniforms, antics, and marching style. Here, a group of Dollies performs a routine.
